  "pages": [
    {
      "text": "Valentina loved the wide brown river that curved behind her colorful town.",
      "image": "page-01.webp",
      "bg": "#E0F7FA",
      "accent": "#00838F",
      "audio": "page-01.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Every morning, she watched silver fish dart through the clear, cool water.",
      "image": "page-02.webp",
      "bg": "#E8F5E9",
      "accent": "#2E7D32",
      "audio": "page-02.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "One day, the water looked dark and smelled strange, and no fish came.",
      "image": "page-03.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF8E1",
      "accent": "#F57F17",
      "audio": "page-03.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Valentina knelt at the bank and scooped some water into a clean glass jar.",
      "image": "page-04.webp",
      "bg": "#E8EAF6",
      "accent": "#3949AB",
      "audio": "page-04.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "She walked along the river asking neighbors, \"When did the water change?\"",
      "image": "page-05.webp",
      "bg": "#FCE4EC",
      "accent": "#C62828",
      "audio": "page-05.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Old Don Ramón said, \"It started three weeks ago, after the new factory opened upstream.\"",
      "image": "page-06.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF3E0",
      "accent": "#E65100",
      "audio": "page-06.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Valentina carried her water sample to the school library and opened every book she could find.",
      "image": "page-07.webp",
      "bg": "#F3E5F5",
      "accent": "#6A1B9A",
      "audio": "page-07.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "She read that dark, oily water means something harmful has been dumped inside it.",
      "image": "page-08.webp",
      "bg": "#E8F5E9",
      "accent": "#1B5E20",
      "audio": "page-08.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Valentina showed her jar and her notes to her teacher, Señora Cruz, who listened carefully.",
      "image": "page-09.webp",
      "bg": "#E0F2F1",
      "accent": "#00695C",
      "audio": "page-09.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Together, the whole class made bright posters that said, \"Save Our River, Save Our Fish!\"",
      "image": "page-10.webp",
      "bg": "#FFFDE7",
      "accent": "#F9A825",
      "audio": "page-10.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Every student wrote a letter to the mayor asking him to stop the factory from dumping waste.",
      "image": "page-11.webp",
      "bg": "#EDE7F6",
      "accent": "#4527A0",
      "audio": "page-11.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "At the town meeting, Valentina stood up tall and read her letter in a clear, strong voice.",
      "image": "page-12.webp",
      "bg": "#FCE4EC",
      "accent": "#AD1457",
      "audio": "page-12.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "The mayor promised to inspect the factory, and soon the river ran clean and the fish came back.",
      "image": "page-13.webp",
      "bg": "#E0F7FA",
      "accent": "#006064",
      "audio": "page-13.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    }
  ]
}